<HEADLINE>
FT  02 JAN 93 / Confusion over new peso
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MEXICO CITY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Confusion reigned in Mexico yesterday as Mexicans were confronted with a new
peso shorn of three zeros, Reuter reports from Mexico City.
Merchants said people were largely unprepared for the currency change, which
was announced last June and took effect at midnight. New coins and bills
reflecting the change are not yet in circulation.
