FT  02 JAN 93 / Cambodia trade sanctions
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PHNOM PENH
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Trade sanctions against the Khmer Rouge have come into effect after the
guerrilla faction launched its most serious attack on UN peacekeepers since
they were deployed in Cambodia, Reuter reports from Phnom Penh.
The sanctions were imposed by the UN Security Council in November because of
the hardline guerrilla group's refusal to comply with the peace accord
signed in Paris in October 1991 to end 13 years of civil war.
